comment: An apparent strengthening of ~ ax-dc (but derived from it) which shows that there is a denumerable sequence ` g ` for any function that maps elements of a set ` A ` to nonempty subsets of ` A ` such that ` g ( x + 1 ) e. F ( g ( x ) ) ` for all ` x e. _om ` . The finitistic version of this can be proven by induction, but the infinite version requires this new axiom. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 25-Jan-2013.)
